body:
Without this, we have to do stuff like:

    long result = THCIndexTensor_(max)(...);

And if we want to change `THCIndexTensor`, we also need to replace `long` everywhere. I thought it would be a good idea to have an `integer` macro instead, just like we have `real`.

body_text:
Without this, we have to do stuff like:
long result = THCIndexTensor_(max)(...);

And if we want to change THCIndexTensor, we also need to replace long everywhere. I thought it would be a good idea to have an integer macro instead, just like we have real.
